<plot>Max(Jack Gilford), an 86-year-old backstage doorman at New York's Belasco Theatre, finds a young actress(Lynne Lipton) rehearsing after hours. They strike up a long conversation in which Max recounts his career in Vaudeville and his cherished encounter with the great Judy Garland the week she played the Palace.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?361628</url></doc>
